
[1]bonny

   BON'NY, a. [L.bonus.]

   1. Handsome; beautiful.

   Till bonny Susan sped across the plain.

   2. Gay; merry; frolicsome; cheerful; blithe.

   Blithe and bonny.

   3. In familiar language, plump, as plump and healthful persons are most
   inclined to mirth.

   [This word is much used in Scotland.]

   BON'NY, n. Among miners, a bed of ore, differing from a squat in being
       round, whereas a squat is flat; or a distinct bed of ore, that
                         communicates with no vein.
